 King Williams Town - Following the arrest of about 15 suspects, including one believed to be the mastermind of an illegal vehicle import syndicate, the Eastern Cape Provincial Anti Corruption Task Team arrested a 32-year-old woman. "Pumza Fayo was arrested t her King Williams Town house on Wednesday for fraud, forgery and money laundering including other charges," said police spokesperson, Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana. "The Lovedale College student is believed to be part of a syndicate that has been involved in fraudulent activities relating to imported cars being illegally registered as rebuilds with the Transport Department and SAPS in the Eastern Cape Province." Brig Kinana said that the female suspect appeared in the Komga Magistrate Court on Thursday on charges relating to the Contravention of the Road Traffic Regulation Act, the Customs and Excise Act, Fraud and Forgery. "She was granted bail and is expected to return to court together with the other co-accused on the 19 September 2019 for trial." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 